A MAN who allegedly raped a gogo (80) has been arrested. The incident happened at Ngquthu Village near Kei Bridge, Butterworth on Wednesday night. Police spokesman Captain Jackson Manatha told the People’s Paper: “The gogo was asleep at about midnight when she suddenly noticed that there was a man in her house. “The suspect allegedly raped the gogo before fleeing the scene. “The victim later told cops she knew her attacker. “The suspect was traced and arrested on Saturday.” He said the suspect would appear in the Butterworth Magistrates Court today, facing a rape charge. Brigadier Trevor Mey, the cluster commander of Butterworth, condemned the alleged rape of a gogo who couldn’t fight and defend herself. Mey praised the Kei Bridge and Butterworth cops for working together to arrest the suspect.